{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect LLR computation in qam16_llr function\n\n### Summary\nThe `qam16_llr` function in the LTE downlink transport channel LLR computation module contains a bug that causes incorrect Log-Likelihood Ratio (LLR) values to be computed for 16-QAM demodulation. This leads to degraded performance in PDSCH decoding when 16-QAM modulation is used.\n\nThe issue is in line 387 of `dlsch_llr_computation.c` where `llr32[1]` incorrectly extracts from index 0 of `llr128[0]` instead of index 1, resulting in duplicate LLR values and missing correct values. This manifests as bit errors during transport block decoding, especially noticeable at higher SNR conditions where 16-QAM is employed.\n\nThe fix corrects the extraction index to ensure all LLR values are properly computed from their respective positions in the unpacked data structures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/dlsch_llr_computation.c`: Corrected extraction index in `qam16_llr` function line 387 from 0 to 1 for `llr32[1]` assignment.\n"
}